import React, { useEffect, useRef, useState } from 'react' import ApexCharts from 'react-apexcharts'; const Dashboard = () => { const totalRevenueRef = useRef(null); const salesAnalyticsRef = useRef(null); const [totalRevenueColors, setTotalRevenueColors] = useState(["#f1556c"]); const [salesAnalyticsColors, setSalesAnalyticsColors] = useState(["#1abc9c", "#4a81d4"]); // Total Revenue Chart Options const totalRevenueOptions = { series: [68], chart: { height: 220, type: "radialBar" }, plotOptions: { radialBar: { hollow: { size: "65%" } } }, colors: totalRevenueColors, labels: ["Revenue"], }; // Sales Analytics Chart Options const salesAnalyticsOptions = { series: [ { name: "Revenue", type: "column", data: [440, 505, 414, 671, 227, 413, 201, 352, 752, 320, 257, 160], }, { name: "Sales", type: "line", data: [23, 42, 35, 27, 43, 22, 17, 31, 22, 22, 12, 16], }, ], chart: { height: 378, type: "line" }, stroke: { width: [2, 3] }, plotOptions: { bar: { columnWidth: "50%" } }, colors: salesAnalyticsColors, dataLabels: { enabled: true, enabledOnSeries: [1] }, labels: [ "01 Jan 2001", "02 Jan 2001", "03 Jan 2001", "04 Jan 2001", "05 Jan 2001", "06 Jan 2001", "07 Jan 2001", "08 Jan 2001", "09 Jan 2001", "10 Jan 2001", "11 Jan 2001", "12 Jan 2001", ], xaxis: { type: "datetime" }, legend: { offsetY: 7 }, grid: { padding: { bottom: 20 } }, fill: { type: "gradient", gradient: { shade: "light", type: "horizontal", shadeIntensity: 0.25, gradientToColors: null, inverseColors: true, opacityFrom: 0.75, opacityTo: 0.75, stops: [0, 0, 0], }, }, yaxis: [ { title: { text: "Net Revenue" } }, { opposite: true, title: { text: "Number of Sales" } }, ], }; useEffect(() => { // Update state with data-colors const totalRevenueDataColors = totalRevenueRef.current?.dataset.colors; totalRevenueDataColors && setTotalRevenueColors(totalRevenueDataColors.split(",")); const salesAnalyticsDataColors = salesAnalyticsRef.current?.dataset.colors; salesAnalyticsDataColors && setSalesAnalyticsColors(salesAnalyticsDataColors.split(",")); }, []); useEffect(() => { // Initialize APEXCHARTS instances const totalRevenueChart = new ApexCharts(totalRevenueRef.current as any, totalRevenueOptions as any); totalRevenueChart.render(); const salesAnalyticsChart = new ApexCharts(salesAnalyticsRef.current as any, salesAnalyticsOptions as any); salesAnalyticsChart.render(); }, [totalRevenueOptions, salesAnalyticsOptions]); // useEffect(() => { // // Find the total-revenue element // const totalRevenueElement = document.querySelector("#total-revenue") as HTMLDivElement; // // Check if the element exists before accessing its dataset // if (totalRevenueElement) { // const totalRevenueDataColors = totalRevenueElement.dataset.colors; // totalRevenueChart.render(); // } // // Similarly, do the same for the sales-analytics element // const salesAnalyticsElement = document.querySelector("#sales-analytics") as HTMLDivElement; // if (salesAnalyticsElement) { // const salesAnalyticsDataColors = salesAnalyticsElement.dataset.colors; // salesAnalyticsDataColors && setSalesAnalyticsColors(salesAnalyticsDataColors.split(",")); // const salesAnalyticsChart = new ApexCharts(salesAnalyticsElement, salesAnalyticsOptions); // salesAnalyticsChart.render(); // } // }, []); return (
